casebody.data:
Lilian H. FOSDICK v. B. F. KEITH-COLUMBUS COMPANY. No. 7936. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. March 16, 1938. Robert Fosdick, of Cincinnati, Ohio, for appellant. Kenneth B. Johnston, of Columbus, Ohio, and Ulmer, Berne & Gordon, of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal herein be, and the same is, dismissed, pursuant to motion of appellee.
